# React / TSX standards (daily-magic)

## Imports

- Import named exports from `react`; use `import type` for types.
- Use `@/` path alias for `src/` imports.

## Organization

- Route pages and layouts: `src/app/`
- Feature modules: `src/features/`
- Shared UI: `src/components/` (TailAdmin)
- Hooks: `src/hooks/`
- Server utilities: `src/lib/`

## Components

- PascalCase component names; camelCase for hooks and handlers.
- Extract layout and business logic into focused child components and hooks.
- Prefer function components; use `memo` only when profiling shows benefit.

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS 4** — utility classes and TailAdmin patterns.
- Do not introduce SCSS modules or `enrg-frontend-styleguide`.

## UI primitives

- Prefer TailAdmin components from `src/components/ui/` (`Button`, `Badge`, `Alert`, form inputs).
- Use native `<button type="button">` with semantics when no shared component fits.
- Never use `<div role="button">` or `<span role="button">`.

## Conditional rendering

- Use component maps: `Record<EnumType, () => ReactElement>` defined outside the component.
- Render with `{COMPONENT_MAP[key]()}`.
- Extract complex JSX into variables or small subcomponents.

## Next.js App Router

- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (state, effects, browser APIs).
- Route handlers in `src/app/api/**/route.ts`.
- Colocate feature-specific sections under `src/features/<Feature>/`.

## State

- `useState` / `useReducer` for local UI state.
- React Context is acceptable for theme/sidebar (TailAdmin pattern).
- Server state via route handlers and `fetch` / Neon client in `src/lib/`.

## Trackers

- Link work to **GitHub issues** or **Linear** issues in branch names and PR descriptions — not Jira PRE tickets.
